Use trigonometric identities to manipulate the expression
{{f}} {{g}}^{ {{p}} } (\theta) {{pm}} {{g}}^{ {{p}} } (\theta) {{h}}
into the form \pm [a(\theta)]^p\,[b(\theta)]^q where a(\theta) and b(\theta) are basic trigonometric functions (or 1), and the exponents p and q are non-negative.
